#### for autologout

Automatically logs out users after a period of inactivity
Configurable in config/initializers/devise.rb:
config.timeout_in = 30.minutes

ession["warden.user.user.key"] = [[user.id], auth_salt]
session[:last_request_at] = Time.current.to_i


On every request, Devise checks:

if session[:last_request_at] < Time.current - timeout_in
  sign_out(current_user)
else
  session[:last_request_at] = Time.current.to_i
end


### for remember me

Logout:

cookies.delete(:remember_user_token)


Password change:

auth_salt changes → existing session invalid


Remember-me cookie is invalidated too (because Devise validates auth_salt on auto-login)

evise also creates a remember-me token:

signed_cookie_value = remember_me_token(user)
cookies.signed[:remember_user_token] = {
  value: signed_cookie_value,
  expires: 2.weeks.from_now
}


Updates DB:

user.update!(remember_created_at: Time.current)

“Remember-me allows persistent login across browser restarts. Devise stores a separate signed cookie with a remember token and remember_created_at. On each visit, Devise validates the cookie, fetches the user, and recreates the session, making current_user available even after the session expired.”


####  for recoverable

t.string   :reset_password_token
t.datetime :reset_password_sent_at

Forgot Password Request
          ↓
Generate raw token → hash → save reset_password_token & reset_password_sent_at
          ↓
Send raw token via email link
          ↓
User clicks link → Devise hashes token → compare with DB
          ↓
Token valid & not expired?
  ↓               ↓
Yes → show reset form  No → error / expired
          ↓
User submits new password
          ↓
Update encrypted_password, clear reset_password_token & reset_password_sent_at
          ↓
Optionally log in user, invalidate old sessions (auth_salt)

